:{{DIcon}} Has your dad gone back to the front lines?
::'''Lila:''' Ah... yes, the holiday went by too quickly. I feel like I barely spent any time with him.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why don't you visit him on the front lines?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504049304-->
:::'''Lila:''' I've thought about it, but my dad says it's dangerous and not a place for a girl like me.
:::'''Lila:''' Hmph, I'm not a kid anymore. I've grown up.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It is dangerous, truly.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} In your father's eyes, you'll always be his little girl.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504049308-->
:::'''Lila:''' Well, since you put it that way, I guess I'll just wait patiently for his next break.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} He should be retiring soon.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504049310-->
:::'''Lila:''' He keeps postponing his retirement, saying the unit can't function without him. Honestly, you'd think he was a general or something.
:::'''Lila:''' I understand that Dad has been in the military for decades and has a strong bond with it, but Mom and I really miss him too.
:::'''Lila:''' I hope this time he can retire, he's not getting any younger.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504049313-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504049313-->
::'''Lila:''' If you go to the front lines next time, please tell my dad to work peacefully and not worry, as I'll take good care of Mom and wait for his safe return.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
